Moreover, experimenting with different normalization techniques, such as LayerNorm or BatchNorm, could stabilize the training process and improve convergence rates.

Lastly, adjusting the ratio parameter itself can be considered. A higher ratio reduces the amount of squeezing, which might retain more channel-wise information but at the cost of increased computation.

